{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.30",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 30 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:1",
      "text": "But now the youngest have laughed me to scorn, now they reprove me in their turn, whose fathers I set at nought; whom I did not deem worthy to be with my shepherd dogs.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:2",
      "text": "Yea, why had I the strength of their hands? for them the full term of life was lost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:3",
      "text": "One is childless in want and famine, such as they that fled but lately the distress and misery of drought.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:4",
      "text": "Who compass the salt places on the sounding shore, who had salt herbs for their food, and were dishonourable and of no repute, in want of every good thing; who also ate roots of trees by reason of great hunger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:5",
      "text": "Thieves have risen up against me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:6",
      "text": "whose houses were the caves of the rocks, who lived under the wild shrubs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:7",
      "text": "They will cry out among the rustling bushes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:8",
      "text": "They are sons of fools and vile men, whose name and glory are quenched from off the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:9",
      "text": "But now I am their music, and they have me for a by-word.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:10",
      "text": "And they stood aloof and abhorred me, and spared not to spit in my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:11",
      "text": "For he has opened his quiver and afflicted me: they also have cast off the restraint of my presence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:12",
      "text": "They have risen up against me on the right hand of their offspring; they have stretched out their foot, and directed against me the ways of their destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:13",
      "text": "My paths are ruined; for they have stripped off my raiment: he has shot at me with his weapons.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:14",
      "text": "And he has pleaded against me as he will: I am overwhelmed with pains.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:15",
      "text": "My pains return upon me; my hope is gone like the wind, and my safety as a cloud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:16",
      "text": "Even now my life shall be poured forth upon me; and days of anguish seize me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:17",
      "text": "And by night my bones are confounded; and my sinews are relaxed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:18",
      "text": "With great force my disease has taken hold of my garment: it has compassed me as the collar of my coat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:19",
      "text": "And thou hast counted me as clay; my portion is in dust and ashes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:20",
      "text": "And I have cried to thee, but thou hearest me not: but they stood still, and observed me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:21",
      "text": "They attacked me also without mercy: thou hast scourged me with a strong hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:22",
      "text": "And thou hast put me to grief, and hast cast me away from safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:23",
      "text": "For I know that death will destroy me: for the earth is the house appointed for every mortal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:24",
      "text": "Oh then that I might lay hands upon myself, or at least ask another, and he should do this for me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:25",
      "text": "Yet I wept over every helpless man; I groaned when I saw a man in distress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:26",
      "text": "But I, when I waited for good things, behold, days of evils came the more upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:27",
      "text": "My belly boiled, and would not cease: the days of poverty prevented me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:28",
      "text": "I went mourning without restraint: and I have stood and cried out in the assembly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:29",
      "text": "I am become a brother of monsters, and a companion of ostriches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:30",
      "text": "And my skin has been greatly blackened, and my bones are burned with heat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.30.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:31",
      "text": "My harp also has been turned into mourning, and my song into my weeping.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
